RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUSTOM PRAYER set the pace in the three path as rivals on either side pressed, cleared while changing leads inside the quarter pole, then tired in the closing stages, yet lasted safely. GOT ME A CHRYSLER broke slowly, laid off of the pace in the three path, swung five wide while picking up stride entering the lane, rallied while hanging on his left lead, and closed in belatedly on the tiring leader in the late stages. HAPPY SEASON stalked along the inside, tugged behind the leaders, remained rank entering the turn, pursued from just off of the fence around the bend, took aim on place in the three path in upper stretch after the leader kicked clear, bid for that position approaching midstretch, but was outkicked leaving the furlong pole. INSPECTOR ED tracked between horses while in the three path around the turn, and kept on. REECEMANIA vied for the lead along the inside, but failed to keep pace with his outer counterpart leaving the quarter pole, and gave way. BUCK DOLL TAYLOR lacked speed five wide, then shied from an inner rival entering the lane, and weakened. VALID EARLY got a bit crowded between horses while slow into stride, lagged behind in the two path, and never got involved. ROYAL UNLIMITED pressed the top pair from the four path around the turn, but weakened between horses in upper stretch while hanging on his left lead.

FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES OVER A MILE SINCE AUGUST 16, 2022. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 16 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where En tered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLOR FAST broke a step slowly, trailed along the inside, rallied inside of foes in upper stretch, shifted outside of the leaders at the furlong grounds, and rallied to strike the front at the wire. CABERTOSS tracked two wide and from between horses, stalked down the backstretch, split the leaders to bid at the five sixteenths pole, drew clear in upper stretch, but was nailed at the wire by an outer bidder. TRIVISTA tracked along the inside, then chased in the three path in upper stretch to gain place in the final furlong, but was outkicked late. TIO BLAS lacked speed in the three to four paths, swung five wide entering the lane, but shied from an inner rival at the furlong grounds, flopped back to his left lead in the aftermath, and leveled off. THE GRAY BLUR pressed in the five path into the first turn before deciding to tuck inside of the pace setter at the seven furlong pole, inched forward to reach the front approaching the five furlong marker, showed the way along the inside into the far turn, but was confronted turning for home, headed in upper stretch, and gave way at the furlong grounds. PLEMMONSTON hopped slightly at the start while off slowly, laid off of the pace in the three to four paths around the first turn, then in the five path around the far turn, and made little impact. CAP ROCK MINER set the pace while intentionally staying four to five paths off of the inside into the first turn, got headed by an inner rival approaching the five furlong grounds, stalked into the far turn, but weakened in the three path and between horses at the five sixteenths pole, and was eased through the final furlong. BLURT prompted the pace in the six path, stalked in the four path into the far turn, but faded between horses entering the lane before being eased.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR FREDDIE MAC was sharp leaving the gates, moved over to the rail early, was able to set the pace, was never challenged through out the race, was driven down the lane and finished strong. G'WILDCAT stalked the leader from the second position, was urged to advance around the half mile pole, was driven hard around the three eighths pole and down the lane but couldn't catch the leader today but was able to place while running gamely. AVAILABLE STAR was back early, moved up in between horses on the back side in the three path, stayed 3 wide in the turn, swung eight wide out of the turn entering the lane, was kept to task and was able to out finish other foes while up for show. COHERE was allowed to fall away from the field for the first half of the race, was asked to run at the half mile pole, responded with a long advancing drive along the rail but had to much to do late and didn't have enough. BINDING AGREEMENT was off a step slow, was urged to catch up, had to steady a bit while establishing position, was moved in between horses in the three path, while being asked, responded and improved his position while still being wide, was five wide down the stretch while still gaining ground, drifted out late and flattened out. JANETS JAY JAY was placed along the rail within striking distance for the first half of the race , was asked to pick it up and responded through out the turn, started to tire in the lane but was driven hard and was never able to gain on the leaders. SCHNELL was allowed to settle in the back of the the pack early, was asked to move closer to the leaders from the outside but never rallied.
